{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"[G3 child-coverage audit — parent safe-luge-nog/b4d4-3369-6dd2-41e6, THIS child (908c link-consumer) vs whole roster (908c link-consumer + ba2c parent-consumer)]\n\n4-bucket audit of parent SC/AC vs the children, with every flagged absence cross-checked against the WHOLE roster:\n\n- SC1 (provider-agnostic primitive consumed by BOTH parent + link removal, no Jira logic in gate): FULLY (joint) — 908c consumes the gate on the LINK path (`_diff_links` managed-ref-gated REMOVE; never-managed Jira link adopted inbound); ba2c consumes it on the PARENT CLEAR path. Both halves present.\n- AC1 (reducer maintains/folds managed_refs: monotonic, sorted, never reduced by UNLINK): STRUCTURAL — parent Scope explicitly retains \"the reducer managed_refs field + compaction preservation + byte-parity\" as its OWN in-scope primitive-build work; consumers only READ the set. Not delegated to children, so not a child-attributable gap.\n- AC2 (absent managed_refs → seed from deps+parent_id; pre-feature-compacted test): STRUCTURAL — parent Scope explicitly retains \"migration-seeding.\" Seeding/its test are parent-owned.\n- AC3 (managed_refs survives compact_ticket; compact-then-reconcile test): COVERED behaviorally on the consumer paths — 908c AC5 \"survives a compaction boundary\" + ba2c \"across a compaction boundary\"; the restore mechanism (process_snapshot) is parent-side.\n- AC4 (SNAPSHOT byte-parity / deterministic serialization): STRUCTURAL — parent-owned serialization, in parent Scope.\n- AC5 (shared should_propagate_removal gate exists, provider-agnostic, defaults empty→False, unit-tested REMOVE-vs-ADOPT): gate existence + its OWN unit tests are STRUCTURAL (parent Scope: \"the shared provider-agnostic gate helper (with its own unit tests)\"); the REMOVE-vs-ADOPT DECISION is additionally exercised jointly through the consumers (908c link path, ba2c parent path). Covered.\n- AC6 (operator-facing regression: unlink a managed ref, two reconcile passes, stays removed — churn observably fixed): COVERED (joint) — 908c AC5 \"local-unlink of a managed link emits an outbound remove and is not re-added inbound\" is exactly the churn-fixed regression for the LINK kind; ba2c covers the PARENT kind (human-set parent adopted; managed parent CLEAR converges). No roster gap.\n- AC7 (docs/ documents the pattern + future reclamation hook as template): STRUCTURAL — parent Scope explicitly retains \"docs establishing the reusable pattern.\"\n\nAbsence cross-check: every parent criterion is either (a) jointly covered by the two named CONSUMERS (SC1, AC4 decision, AC3 durability, AC6 regression) or (b) parent-owned in-scope primitive-build work the parent's Scope deliberately retains rather than delegating (AC1, AC2, byte-parity, gate unit-tests, docs). This container is a primitive-building story that carves reducer/seeding/byte-parity/gate-helper/docs into its OWN scope and tracks only the two consumer integrations as children. This child (link consumer) fully covers its half; sibling ba2c covers the parent half. No uncovered parent criterion is attributable to the children.\n\nResult: G3 CLEAN (empty findings)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782537682632498001,"uuid":"c06e30f2-83eb-4ad4-af5a-8c981e1d965c"}